# Canonical Policy Bootstrap

This repository has one canonical long-form operating policy: root `CLAUDE.md` (SDLC governance
brain + engineering operating system).

Before doing analysis, planning, implementation, review, testing, release work, or documentation
work, read `CLAUDE.md` and follow it as binding company policy.

File precedence:

1. `CLAUDE.md` — canonical long-form policy.
2. `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — the active Cursor ruleset (must stay aligned with `CLAUDE.md`).
3. `AGENTS.md` — the agent bootstrap file.
4. `CODEX.md` / `cursor.md` — tool-facing bootstrap mirrors.
5. `.cursorrules` — legacy compatibility shim only.

If any of these files ever differ, `CLAUDE.md` wins. When two rules overlap, the stricter one
applies.

Whenever a new permanent rule, workflow, quality gate, architecture constraint, testing
expectation, release rule, or operational rule is discovered, update `CLAUDE.md` first, then keep
all mirror files aligned in the same delivery stream.
